<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900928-0038</DOCNO><DOCID>900928-0038.</DOCID><HL>   International Brief -- Ing. C. Olivetti andamp; Co.:   Consolidated Pretax Profit   For the First Half Fell 41%</HL><DATE>09/28/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A11</SO><CO>   I.OLV</CO><IN>OFFICE EQUIPMENT (OFF)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   Ing. C. Olivetti andamp; Co. of Italy, an office automationequipment maker, reported that first-half consolidated pretaxprofit fell 41% to 60.9 billion lire ($51.9 million) from102.6 billion lire a year earlier, continuing a 3 1/2-yearearnings slide.   Operating profit fell 35% to 102.1 billion lire from 156.4billion lire.</LP><TEXT>   Revenue rose 5.8% to 4.167 trillion lire from 3.938trillion lire.   Carlo De Benedetti, chairman and the controllingshareholder, blamed the earnings drop on tough marketconditions, a continuing squeeze in profit margins and anunfavorable exchange rate for the lira. But the companyclaimed it fared much better than most of its European andU.S. competitors, and predicted it will continue to outpaceother computer makers for the rest of the year, though itdidn't give a specific earnings forecast.</TEXT></DOC>